p\u00e1nica''] ''Biblioteca Nacional de Espa\u00f1a''  {{in lang|es}}.\n* [https://wheniwasachildinferrol.neocities.org/RosaliaDeCastro/ ''Translation from Galician to English of 11 poems by Rosal\u00eda de Castro'']  {{in lang|en}}.\n* {{Librivox author |id=12179}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Galician Literature Day}}\n{{Romanticism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Castro, Rosalia de}}\n[[Category:1837 births]]\n[[Category:1885 deaths]]\n[[Category:Spanish women poets]]\n[[Category:Galician poets]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic writers]]\n[[Category:People from Santiago de Compostela]]\n[[Category:Burials in Galicia]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in Spain]]\n[[Category:Galician-language writers]]\n[[Category:Galician Literature Day]]\n[[Category:Galician women writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Spanish poets]]\n[[Category:19th-century Spanish women writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Spanish writers]]\n", "name_user": "JoseFranco", "label": "safe", "comment": "She was a Spanish writer, from a region of Spain named as Galicia.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rosal%C3%ADa_de_Castro"}
{"title_page": "Almost Adults", "text_new": "{{short description|2016 Canadian film directed by Sarah Rotella}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Almost Adults\n| director = Sarah Rotella\n| producer = Rebecca Swift\n| writer = Adrianna DiLonardo\n| starring = [[Natasha Negovanlis]]<br>[[Elise Bauman]]<br>Justin Gerhard<br>Winny Clarke\n| cinematography = Ryan Glover\n| editing = Haya Waseem\n| studio = Unsolicited Pictures\n| distributor = Gravitas Ventures\n| released = {{film date|2016|05|28|Toronto LGBT Film Festival|2017|2|7}}\n| runtime = 90 minutes\n| country = Canada\n| language = English\n}}\n\n'''''Almost Adults''''' is a 2016 Canadian [[comedy film]] directed by Sarah Rotella and starring [[Natasha Negovanlis]]. The film is a platonic love story about two lifelong best friends struggling to keep their friendship together as their lives head in different directions. It was written by Adrianna DiLonardo and [[Elise Bauman]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2015/03/growing-up-without-growing-apart-is-hard-for-almost-adults-63916/|title=Growing Up Without Growing Apart is Hard for 'Almost Adults'|date=March 19, 2015|website=[[Indiewire]]|language=en|access-date=July 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Premise ==\nThe film follows two best friends in their final year of college while they transition into adulthood. One embraces her sexuality and tries to catch up on everything she has missed during her teenage years, while the other ends a long-term relationship with her boyfriend and discovers her life isn't going as planned. Both struggle to keep their friendship together as they begin growing apart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://almostadultsmovie.com/#synopsis|title=Almost Adults Movie - See the official trailer now!|website=Almost Adults Movie|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{Cast listing|\n* [[Natasha Negovanlis]] as Cassie\n* [[Elise Bauman]] as Mackenzie\n* Justin Gerhard as Levi\n* Winny Clarke as Elliot\n* Mark Matechuk as Matthew\n* Pujaa Pandey as Tasha\n* Delphine Roussel as Diane\n* Meredith Heinrich as Lisa\n* Christina Song as Juliana\n* Daryl Marks as John \n* David J Phillips as Dr. Reese\n}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe film was shot in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], over 11 days.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://nowtoronto.com/movies/features/almost-adults-toronto-sarah-rotello-ariadne-dilonardo/|title=Toronto-based Almost Adults filmmakers say no thanks to the theatrical distribution deal|date=2017-02-06|work=NOW Magazine|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/screens/2016-10-16/austin-film-festival-review-almost-adults/|title=Austin Film Festival Review: ''Almost Adults''|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nAlmost Adults (2016) was fully funded through Kickstarter in 2015, reaching 305% of its goal in 30 days. The film won IndieWire's Project Of The Year in 2015, and was a part of the Tribeca Film Institute Network. Almost Adults premiered at the InsideOut Film Festival where it won \"Best Canadian Feature: Honourable Mention\" and went on to screen at 12 more festivals worldwide, while garnering buzz online. It was one of the top 20 most talked about film on Tumblr on three occasions according to Tumblr's Fandometrics<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thefandometrics.tumblr.com/post/125205388074/movies-week-ending-july-27th-2015-ant-man-1|title=Tumblr Fandometrics \u2014 Movies Week Ending July 27th, 2015 Ant-Man +1 ...|website=Tumblr Fandometrics |access-date=2018-05-07}}</ref> (in the company of major blockbusters including Avengers, Mockingjay and Terminator), and the trailer reached 2.3 million organic views. The film was acquired by Gravitas Ventures and released on 24 VOD platforms on February 7, 2017 and Netflix in 13 countries including Canada and the United States, and made it into the \"Popular on Netflix\" category. Almost Adults was in the top 10 best-selling list for pre-orders on iTunes, and on the week of release was #23 in the U.S.\n\n== Reception ==\nAlmost Adults had its world premiere to a sold-out screening at Toronto's InsideOut Film Festival, and a 2nd sold out screening for the U.S premiere at [[Outfest]].\n\n[[BuzzFeed|Buzzfeed]] included ''Almost Adults'' in their list \"25 Films That Have Made A Difference To The LGBT Community\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/ishabassi/a-long-way-to-go-but-a-positive-step-forward|title=25 Films That Have Made A Difference To The LGBT Community|work=BuzzFeed|access-date=2018-05-07|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[Autostraddle]] praised the film for flipping the script on classic lesbian movie tropes, commenting that the story wasn't about either of the characters having feelings for the other, or Mack coming out and Cassie not accepting her, but rather that they were both \"young and selfish and trying to figure out who they were and how they fit into each other's lives.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autostraddle.com/almost-adults-is-a-cute-lesbian-movie-to-add-to-the-very-short-list-of-actually-good-lesbian-movies-368802/|title=\"Almost Adults\" Is a Cute Lesbian Movie to Add to the Very Short List of Actually Good Lesbian Movies|date=2017-02-10|work=Autostraddle|access-date=2017-09-24|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Curve (magazine)|Curve]] said the \"film takes a light hearted and comedic approach at portraying the struggles all young adults face.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.curvemag.com/Cinema/Almost-Adults-661/|title=Almost Adults|last=Davis|first=Annalese|access-date=2017-09-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' gave a positive review, stating  that \"... above all else, it excels at remaining inoffensive, which isn't always the best approach for an adult comedy dealing with high-stakes personal issues.\" The review went on to praise Negovanlis and Bauman's chemistry, but stated \"the comedic quotient drops noticeably in scenes with mostly underwhelming supporting cast members.\" The review criticized how predictable the film was, but gave praise to Rotella for \"[having] an eye for visual humor and comedic timing.\"<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/almost-adults-outfest-review-911724|title='Almost Adults': Outfest Review|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en}}</ref>\n\nDorkShelf.com Casey Reid wrote a positive review in regards to the movie both by praising the movie itself and the director, \"Almost Adults is a cohesive debut film that shows our digital age's love and relationships in a fresh way, signalling a promising career for Sarah Rotella.\" She also acknowledges how the movie is such a great addition in the cinematic industry, \"What makes Almost Adults refreshing is that it's reflexive of contemporary queer culture, albeit white centric, in a way that signals a shift in queer cinema. While it does not quite touch on ideas of nostalgia so entrenched in queer cinema, it seems to directly reflect how young people connect and disconnect with themselves and each other.\" However she does mention how the movie does \" lack depth in certain areas\" she does conclude that \"it's tight editing and interesting shot choices create easy access for audience members.\"<ref>http://dorkshelf.com/2016/05/25/inside-out-2016-almost-adults-review/</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of LGBT films directed by women]]\n* [[Female gaze]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|4686862}}\n\n[[Category:LGBT-related drama films]]\n[[Category:Canadian films]]\n[[Category:Canadian LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Canadian drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2016 Canadian film directed by Sarah Rotella}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Almost Adults\n| director = Sarah Rotella\n| producer = Rebecca Swift\n| writer = Adrianna DiLonardo\n| starring = [[Natasha Negovanlis]]<br>[[Elise Bauman]]<br>Justin Gerhard<br>Winny Clarke\n| cinematography = Ryan Glover\n| editing = Haya Waseem\n| studio = Unsolicited Pictures\n| distributor = Gravitas Ventures\n| released = {{film date|2016|05|28|Toronto LGBT Film Festival|2017|2|7}}\n| runtime = 90 minutes\n| country = Canada\n| language = English\n}}\n\n'''''Almost Adults''''' is a 2016 Canadian [[comedy film]] directed by Sarah Rotella and starring [[Natasha Negovanlis]]. The film is a platonic love story about two life long best friends struggling to keep their friendship together as their lives head in different directions. It was written by Adrianna DiLonardo and [[Elise Bauman]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2015/03/growing-up-without-growing-apart-is-hard-for-almost-adults-63916/|title=Growing Up Without Growing Apart is Hard for 'Almost Adults'|date=March 19, 2015|website=[[Indiewire]]|language=en|access-date=July 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Premise ==\nThe film follows two best friends in their final year of college while they transition into adulthood. One embraces her sexuality and tries to catch up on everything she has missed during her teenage years, while the other ends a long term relationship with her boyfriend and discovers her life isn't going as planned. Both struggle to keep their friendship together as they begin growing apart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://almostadultsmovie.com/#synopsis|title=Almost Adults Movie - See the official trailer now!|website=Almost Adults Movie|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{Cast listing|\n* [[Natasha Negovanlis]] as Cassie\n* [[Elise Bauman]] as Mackenzie\n* Justin Gerhard as Levi\n* Winny Clarke as Elliot\n* Mark Matechuk as Matthew\n* Pujaa Pandey as Tasha\n* Delphine Roussel as Diane\n* Meredith Heinrich as Lisa\n* Christina Song as Juliana\n* Daryl Marks as John \n* David J Phillips as Dr. Reese\n}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe film was shot in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], over 11 days.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://nowtoronto.com/movies/features/almost-adults-toronto-sarah-rotello-ariadne-dilonardo/|title=Toronto-based Almost Adults filmmakers say no thanks to the theatrical distribution deal|date=2017-02-06|work=NOW Magazine|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/screens/2016-10-16/austin-film-festival-review-almost-adults/|title=Austin Film Festival Review: ''Almost Adults''|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nAlmost Adults (2016) was fully funded through Kickstarter in 2015, reaching 305% of its goal in 30 days. The film won IndieWire's Project Of The Year in 2015, and was a part of the Tribeca Film Institute Network. Almost Adults premiered at the InsideOut Film Festival where it won \"Best Canadian Feature: Honourable Mention\" and went on to screen at 12 more festivals worldwide, while garnering buzz online. It was one of the top 20 most talked about film on Tumblr on three occasions according to Tumblr\u2019s Fandometrics<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thefandometrics.tumblr.com/post/125205388074/movies-week-ending-july-27th-2015-ant-man-1|title=Tumblr Fandometrics \u2014 Movies Week Ending July 27th, 2015 Ant-Man +1 ...|website=Tumblr Fandometrics |access-date=2018-05-07}}</ref> (in the company of major blockbusters including Avengers, Mockingjay and Terminator), and the trailer reached 2.3 million organic views. The film was acquired by Gravitas Ventures and released on 24 VOD platforms on February 7, 2017 and Netflix in 13 countries including Canada and the United States, and made it into the \"Popular on Netflix\" category. Almost Adults was in the top 10 best-selling list for pre-orders on iTunes, and on the week of release was #23 in the U.S.\n\n== Reception ==\nAlmost Adults had its world premiere to a sold-out screening at Toronto's InsideOut Film Festival, and a 2nd sold out screening for the U.S premiere at [[Outfest]].\n\n[[BuzzFeed|Buzzfeed]] included ''Almost Adults'' in their list \"25 Films That Have Made A Difference To The LGBT Community\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/ishabassi/a-long-way-to-go-but-a-positive-step-forward|title=25 Films That Have Made A Difference To The LGBT Community|work=BuzzFeed|access-date=2018-05-07|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[Autostraddle]] praised the film for flipping the script on classic lesbian movie tropes, commenting that the story wasn't about either of the characters having feelings for the other, or Mack coming out and Cassie not accepting her, but rather that they were both \"young and selfish and trying to figure out who they were and how they fit into each other's lives.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.autostraddle.com/almost-adults-is-a-cute-lesbian-movie-to-add-to-the-very-short-list-of-actually-good-lesbian-movies-368802/|title=\"Almost Adults\" Is a Cute Lesbian Movie to Add to the Very Short List of Actually Good Lesbian Movies|date=2017-02-10|work=Autostraddle|access-date=2017-09-24|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Curve (magazine)|Curve]] said the \"film takes a light hearted and comedic approach at portraying the struggles all young adults face.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.curvemag.com/Cinema/Almost-Adults-661/|title=Almost Adults|last=Davis|first=Annalese|access-date=2017-09-24|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' gave a positive review, stating  that \"... above all else, it excels at remaining inoffensive, which isn't always the best approach for an adult comedy dealing with high-stakes personal issues.\" The review went on to praise Negovanlis and Bauman's chemistry, but stated \"the comedic quotient drops noticeably in scenes with mostly underwhelming supporting cast members.\" The review criticized how predictable the film was, but gave praise to Rotella for \"[having] an eye for visual humor and comedic timing.\"<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/almost-adults-outfest-review-911724|title='Almost Adults': Outfest Review|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2017-09-03|language=en}}</ref>\n\nDorkShelf.com Casey Reid wrote a positive review in regards to the movie both by praising the movie itself and the director, \"Almost Adults is a cohesive debut film that shows our digital age's love and relationships in a fresh way, signalling a promising career for Sarah Rotella.\" She also acknowledges how the movie is such a great addition in the cinematic industry, \"What makes Almost Adults refreshing is that it's reflexive of contemporary queer culture, albeit white centric, in a way that signals a shift in queer cinema. While it does not quite touch on ideas of nostalgia so entrenched in queer cinema, it seems to directly reflect how young people connect and disconnect with themselves and each other.\" However she does mention how the movie does \" lack depth in certain areas\" she does conclude that \"it's tight editing and interesting shot choices create easy access for audience members.\"<ref>http://dorkshelf.com/2016/05/25/inside-out-2016-almost-adults-review/</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of LGBT films directed by women]]\n* [[Female gaze]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|4686862}}\n\n[[Category:LGBT-related drama films]]\n[[Category:Canadian films]]\n[[Category:Canadian LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Canadian drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: long term \u2192 long-term, life long \u2192 lifelong, \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Almost_Adults"}
